14/05/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Parliament Speaker Bulent Arinc will attend the Parliamentary Summit of the Council of Europe (CoE) early next week in Strasbourg.
The summit will host parliament speakers from 45 CoE member countries and observers.
It will focus on levels of democracy in member states and the use of technological advances to strengthen democratic procedures.
In other news, Turkish State Minister Kursad Tuzmen is in Paris to attend the OECD's annual ministerial council meeting.
The agenda includes international trade negotiations issues, effects of demographic changes on the economies of member countries and problems related to unemployment.
(Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News, NTV - 13/05/04)
